step 1 : Build JAR

mvn clean package -DskipTests

step 2 : add MongoDB and Redis as services in your docker-compose.yml and stop running them on localhost

step 3 : create dockerfile

step 4 : Build image + run everything

docker-compose up --build

#Note
docker-compose up --build — use this when you made code changes (rebuilds the image with new JAR)
docker-compose up — use this when nothing changed, just want to start containers

docker-compose down -v
use -v to avoid the Zookeeper stale node issue next time you start up.